inode number - it is a number that works like index for unix.this index tells unix about the location of the file.

stroage of files 
each inode entry in the inode table consists of 13 addresses each numbered from 0 to 12,which specicfy completely where the file are stored.
first 10 addresses point to 1 KB block.
11th also contains an address of 1 KB block.this block do contain file instead it consists of 256 four byte slots which stores 256 more addresses.each of these 256 address can point to a 1 KB block.
